"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891413","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-30","<p>All eligible single source contracts placed by the Submarine Delivery Agency will be covered by the single source procurement legislation. The Single Source Regulations Office will have the same role on these contracts as they do with other such contracts.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-04-30T16:05:11.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891413/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891413/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891413/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-25","Submarine Delivery Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the implications are for the work of the Single Source Regulations Office on the procurement of the establishment of the Submarine Delivery Agency.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","137972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891414","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Department does not hold information on the regulatory compliance of broadcasters. This information has been requested from the independent regulator, Ofcom, and we will write to the Rt Hon member following the outcome of these discussions. A copy of the letter will be placed in the House library.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","137941","2018-05-03T15:19:48.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891414/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891414/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891414/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-25","Comcast","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many times (a) Comcast and (b) any subsidiary of Comcast which holds broadcasting licences has been found to be in breach of the Broadcasting Code.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","137940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891415","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Department does not hold information on the regulatory compliance of broadcasters. This information has been requested from the independent regulator, Ofcom, and we will write to the Rt Hon member following the outcome of these discussions. A copy of the letter will be placed in the House library.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","137940","2018-05-03T15:19:48.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891415/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891415/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891415/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-25","Comcast","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many times (a) Comcast and (b) any subsidiary of Comcast which holds broadcasting licences has been sanctioned by Ofcom under the Broadcasting Code in the last 10 years; and for what reason those sanctions were imposed.","false","Biography information for Mr Nigel Evans","Ribble Valley","Mr Nigel Evans","137941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891416","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-30","<p>Sentinel aircraft are currently deployed in the Middle East. They support Op SHADER and other tasking, as dictated by strategic necessity.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-04-30T15:53:26.41Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891416/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891416/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891416/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-25","Islamic State: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether Raytheon Sentinel R1 radar surveillance aircraft are currently deployed in support of Operation Shader.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","137973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891417","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-30","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the reply given by my noble Friend, the Minister of State for Defence, the right hon. Earl Howe to the noble Lord, Lord Moonie of Bennochy to Question HL3584 in the House of Lords.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-04-30T15:59:52.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891417/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891417/answer","HL3584_Sentinal_Aircraft.docx","HL3584_Sentinal_Aircraft.docx","HL3584 - WQnA extract on Sentinel Aircraft","HL3584 - WQnA extract on Sentinel Aircraft","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891417/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-25","Sentinel Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department plans to take to maintain capabilities currently provided by RAF Sentinel R1 aircraft after 2021.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","137974"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891418","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-30","<p>In June 2014 the majority of magistrates’ court work at Bedford Magistrates’ Court (at the Shire Hall building) was centralised into Luton Magistrates’ Court. This was following a judicially-led consultation on revised listing arrangements, which was conducted in 2013.</p><p> </p><p>Magistrates’ family cases, along with civil and tribunal cases, continue to be heard at the court. The Shire Hall building will only close subject to a public consultation, which will be published in due course.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-04-30T16:50:23.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891418/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891418/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891418/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-25","Magistrates' Courts: Bedford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when Bedford Magistrate’s Court was closed; and to where the services of that court were relocated.","false","Biography information for Mohammad Yasin","Bedford","Mohammad Yasin","138084"
