"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891420","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-04-30","<p>We have been listening to tenants through a process of engagement which finished on 10 April, and over 7,000 people have shared their views across a wide range of concerns.</p><p>We intend to publish the Social Housing Green Paper in the next few months.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-04-30T09:44:54.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891420/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891420/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891420/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-25","Social Rented Housing: Consultation Papers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the answer of 5 February 2018 to Question 125886, when he plans to publish the social housing green paper.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","137908"
