"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891422","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-30","<p>It is not possible to provide an answer to this question from centrally held data as this does not differentiate between different court locations in Bedford. Since the employment tribunal building in Bedford ceased to hold public hearings in September 2017, the administration of cases has moved to Watford and has not differentiated between cases heard in that office and in Bedford.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-04-30T16:55:06.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891422/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891422/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891422/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-25","Employment Tribunals Service: Bedford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many employment tribunal hearings have been listed at Shire Hall in (a) 2015–16, (b) 2016-17 and (c) 2017 to date.","false","Biography information for Mohammad Yasin","Bedford","Mohammad Yasin","138087"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891423","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-30","<p>HM Courts &amp; Tribunals Service is currently considering options regarding the future court estate in Bedfordshire. The Shire Hall building will only close subject to a public consultation regarding the distribution of the work currently heard in the building, which will be published in due course.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-04-30T16:46:03.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891423/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891423/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891423/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-25","Courts: Bedford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what plans his Department has for the future of court services in Bedford when the lease expires on the building that hosts Luton County and Family Court on 9 January 2020; and what provision he has made for court services in Luton and Bedfordshire when that lease expires.","false","Biography information for Mohammad Yasin","Bedford","Mohammad Yasin","138088"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891424","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-30","<p>We plan to publish regular national statistics on Universal Credit, including advances, in the near future. This data is currently going through quality assurance clearance procedures in line with the National Statistics and Official Statistics publication standard.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-04-30T10:32:43.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891424/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891424/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891424/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-25","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 24 January 2018 to Question 123902, how many claims for universal credit were paid an advance of of (a) less than £50, (b) £50.01-£100, (c) £100.01-£150, (d) £150.01-£200, (e) £200.01-£250, (f) £250.01-£300, (g) £300.01-£350, (h) £350.01-£400, (i) £400.01-£450, (j) £450.01-£500, (k) £500-01-£600, (l) £550.01-£660 and (m) greater than £600 in each month from 1 January 2018 up to and including the week beginning 26 March 2018.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","138065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891425","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-30","<p>We plan to publish regular national statistics on Universal Credit, including payment timeliness, in the near future. This data is currently going through quality assurance clearance procedures in line with the National Statistics and Official Statistics publication standard.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","138067","2018-04-30T10:32:44.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891425/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891425/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891425/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-25","Universal Credit: Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 25 January 2018 to Question 124171, what proportion of new claims for universal credit under full service overall received (a) full payment on time or (b) some payment on time from 1 January 2018 up to and including the week beginning 26 March 2018.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","138066"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891426","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-30","<p>We plan to publish regular national statistics on Universal Credit, including payment timeliness, in the near future. This data is currently going through quality assurance clearance procedures in line with the National Statistics and Official Statistics publication standard.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma","138066","2018-04-30T10:32:44.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891426/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891426/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891426/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-25","Universal Credit: Payments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 25 January 2018 to Question 124171, what proportion of new claims for universal credit under full service received (a) full payment on time or (b) some payment on time in each week from 1 January 2018 up to and including the week beginning 26 March 2018.","false","Biography information for Margaret Greenwood","Wirral West","Margaret Greenwood","138067"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891427","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-01","<p>The Clean Growth Strategy made clear that the Government believes the UK will need to legislate for a net zero emissions target at an appropriate point in the future, to provide legal certainty on where the UK is heading.</p><p> </p><p>We will seek the Committee on Climate Change’s (CCC) advice on the implications of Paris Agreement for the UK’s long-term targets, after the release of the IPCC Special Report later this year.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-01T16:35:21.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891427/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891427/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891427/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-25","Climate Change Convention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to align the UK's domestic climate commitments under the Climate Change Act 2008 with the Paris Agreement during the 2017-2019 Parliamentary Session.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","137888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891428","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-02","<p>There are currently no plans to amend the Climate Change Act to include a statutory response time for the publication of carbon plans.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-02T13:58:40.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891428/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891428/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891428/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-25","Carbon Emissions: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, with reference to the report entitled 10 years of the UK Climate Change Act, published by the London School of Economics and Political Science on 30 March, 2018 what assessment he has made of the potential merits of the recommendation in that report to amend the Climate Change Act 2008 to include a statutory response time for carbon plans.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","137889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891429","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-01","<p>The UK is firmly committed to the Paris Agreement and to our emissions reduction and climate finance efforts under it. We have demonstrated our commitment domestically – just last week I announced that we would submit our highly praised Clean Growth Strategy as the UK’s long-term strategy to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC). I also announced our intention to seek the advice of the Committee on Climate Change (CCC) on the implications of the Paris Agreement for the UK’s long-term emissions reduction targets after the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) publishes its Special Report on 1.5<sup>o</sup>C later this year.</p><p> </p><p>The UK is a party to the UNFCCC individually as well as through the EU and we are bound by all the obligations of the Paris Agreement. This includes the requirement to prepare, communicate and maintain successive nationally determined contributions. A decision on the nature of a future UK NDC once we have left the EU is one of a number of issues we are currently considering carefully. We are looking forward to constructive discussions with the EU to ensure that we reach the best deal for the British people and for tackling climate change.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-01T16:35:07.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891429/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891429/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891429/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-25","Climate Change Convention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department plans to submit a new Nationally Determined Contribution (NDC) which is separate from the EU's NDC to the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change as required by the Paris Agreement after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","137890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891430","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-02","<p>The Government is considering all factors in relation to the UK’s future participation, or otherwise, in the EU ETS, in consultation with stakeholders.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-02T13:59:13.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891430/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891430/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891430/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-25","Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of establishing a UK-wide emissions trading system after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","137891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891431","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-02","<p>The Government welcomes the formal agreement earlier this year on reform of the EU ETS for the 2021-30 period (‘Phase IV’). It strikes an effective balance between environmental ambition and protecting the competitiveness of industry. These reforms are expected to result in a more meaningful carbon price and stimulate investment in low-carbon technologies and the support of these reforms is without prejudice to any future decision on UK participation, or otherwise, in the EU ETS after we leave the EU.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-02T14:00:10.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891431/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891431/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891431/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-25","EU Emissions Trading Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of participating in Phase 4 of the EU's emissions trading system after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","137892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891432","Home Office","false","2018-04-30","<p>The introduction of additional qualified informants will be progressed alongside wider Death Certification Reforms contained within the Coroners and Justice Act 2009.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-04-30T14:25:31.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891432/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891432/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891432/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-25","Registration of Births, Deaths, Marriages and Civil Partnerships","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, with reference to the Coroners and Justice Act 2009, what the timetable is bring forward the regulations to amend the list of informants for the registration of a death to include the categories (a) partner of the deceased’ and (b) personal representative of the deceased.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","138022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891433","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-04-30","<p>The Government will be considering how to proceed in relation to proposals made by the Law Commission in the context of any further reforms to the family justice system.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-04-30T17:43:44.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891433/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891433/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891433/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-25","Cohabitation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will bring forward legislative proposals to enable cohabiting couples to share financial and property rights.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","138023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891434","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-30","<p>The Department has not owned any buildings since 2003, and leases all of its estate.</p><p> </p><p>The Department takes our responsibility to ensure all our customers have access to our services without disadvantage very seriously. Every DWP office has been assessed to ensure that we are compliant with the requirements of the Equality Act 2010. Where suitable physical adaptations to buildings are not possible, the Department provides an alternative method of delivering our services where we are made aware that a customer has potential access issues, such as an appointment would be rearranged at a ground floor location or by a home visit.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-30T13:41:51.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891434/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891434/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891434/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-25","Department for Work and Pensions: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what her Department's policy is on disability access to buildings that it (a) owns or (b) manages.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","138057"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891435","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-30","<p>There are no buildings that fail to comply with the Department’s policies on disability access to our services.</p><p> </p><p>The Department takes our responsibility to ensure all our customers have access to our services without disadvantage very seriously. Every DWP office has been assessed to ensure that we are compliant with the requirements of the Equality Act 2010. Where suitable physical adaptations to buildings are not possible, the Department provides an alternative method of delivering our services where we are made aware that a customer has potential access issues, such as an appointment would be rearranged at a ground floor location or by a home visit.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-30T13:42:04.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891435/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891435/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891435/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-25","Department for Work and Pensions: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many of her Department's buildings fail to comply with its policies on disability access; and where those buildings are located.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","138058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891436","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-30","<p>The Department takes our responsibility to ensure all our customers have access to our services without disadvantage very seriously. Every DWP office has been assessed to ensure that we are compliant with the requirements of the Equality Act 2010. Where suitable physical adaptations to buildings are not possible, the Department provides an alternative method of delivering our services where we are made aware that a customer has potential access issues, such as an appointment would be rearranged at a ground floor location or by a home visit.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-30T13:42:16.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891436/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891436/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891436/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-25","Department for Work and Pensions: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what her Department's policy is on disability access to buildings owned or managed by her Department's contractors.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","138059"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891437","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-30","<p>There are no buildings that fail to comply with the Department’s policies on disability access to our services.</p><p> </p><p>The Department takes our responsibility to ensure all our customers have access to our services and facilities without disadvantage very seriously. Every DWP office has been assessed to ensure that we are compliant with the requirements of the Equality Act 2010. Where suitable physical adaptations to buildings are not possible, the Department provides an alternative method of delivering our services where we are made aware that a customer has potential access issues, such as an appointment would be rearranged at a ground floor location or by a home visit.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-30T13:42:44.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891437/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891437/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891437/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-25","Department for Work and Pensions: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many buildings managed by contractors of her Department fail to comply with her Department's disabled access policy; and where those buildings are located.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","138060"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891438","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-30","<p>The Department does not have a policy on ensuring that people accessing our buildings have access to parking within twenty meters as there is no requirement to provide parking facilities for staff or the public.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-30T13:42:45.843Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891438/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891438/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-25","Department for Work and Pensions: Parking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what her Department's policy is on ensuring that people accessing buildings managed by (a) her Department and (b) her Department's contractors have access to parking within twenty metres of those buildings.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","138061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891439","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-30","<p>This information is not held.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-30T14:07:11.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891439/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891439/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-25","Department for Work and Pensions: Parking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of the buildings managed by (a) her Department and (b) her Department's contractors do not have access to parking within 20 metres; and where those buildings are located.","false","Biography information for Neil Gray","Airdrie and Shotts","Neil Gray","138062"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891440","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-30","<p>The Lille Road Health Centre, which is the practice all patients registered with the GP at Hand service are associated with, has a registered list of 24,652 as of March 2018.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-30T13:21:49.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891440/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891440/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-25","GP at Hand","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many patients are registered with the GP at Hand service.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","138110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891441","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-01","<p>These pilots build upon learning from the Housing First Feasibility study Government co-funded in Liverpool City region, published in July 2017, which showed that Housing First could work to end the homelessness of those with the most complex needs, if delivered as an integrated part of wider homelessness services. The report set out a blue print for the necessary mental health provision embedded within the core Housing First Teams and the relationships with other local services necessary to make the approach a success.</p><p>Government committed £28 million at budget 2017 to implement three regional Housing First pilots in the West Midlands, Greater Manchester, and Liverpool City Region.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-05-01T12:33:58.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891441/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891441/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-25","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the wrap-around substance misuse and mental health services that will required to help ensure the targets for Housing First are met.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","138063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891442","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-03","<p>International evidence shows that Housing First can be successful at ending the homelessness of those with the most complex needs. The Government is investing in three regional pilots to test the effectiveness of the approach in England.</p><p>These pilots build upon learning from the Housing First Feasibility study Government co-funded in Liverpool City region, published in July 2017, which showed that Housing First could work to end the homelessness of those with the most complex needs</p><p>Regarding Supported Housing funding reforms, an interim response to the consultation on the models was published on 3 April 2018 and a full response will be published in the summer<em>.</em></p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-05-03T12:50:56.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891442/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891442/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-25","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of Housing First targets to (a) reduce rough sleeping and (b) fund supported housing.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","138064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891443","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-02","<p>Since April 2016 every dog in Great Britain is required to be microchipped with the keeper’s details. Over 90% of dog owners are compliant with the microchipping requirement which allows dogs to be traced back to their keeper and if the dog strays allows dog and keeper to be reunited quickly. There are no plans to reintroduce the dog licence in England.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-05-02T15:09:29.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891443/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891443/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891443/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-25","Dogs: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether his Department has plans to replicate the Northern Ireland dog licencing system in England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Giles Watling","Clacton","Giles Watling","138111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891444","Department for Education","false","2018-04-30","<p>The government response to both the independent review ‘Foster Care in England’ and the Education Select Committee’s report on fostering will be published within the next three months.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-04-30T16:10:03.147Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891444/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891444/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891444/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-25","Foster Care: Government Responses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, when he plans to publish the Government’s response to the reports on foster care in England from the (a) Education Committee and (b) Independent Review on foster care by Sir Martin Narey and Mark Owers.","false","Biography information for Thelma Walker","Colne Valley","Thelma Walker","138103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891445","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-02","<p>Ministers’ diaries are not online so there is no information to report on page views.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-05-02T17:00:05.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891445/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891445/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891445/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-25","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Diaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many page views there were of his Department's Ministerial diaries in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891446","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-05-03","<p>We do not have the means to measure page views for the Department’s ministerial diaries. However the following Department for Exiting the European Union gov.uk pages which contain information on ministerial meetings have had the associated number of page views in total over the last 12 months or since their publication -</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>/government/publications/department-for-exiting-the-european-union-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-october-to-december-2017 – 1349 views</p><p>/government/publications/department-for-exiting-the-european-union-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-and-meetings-july-to-september-2017 - 1382 views</p><p>/government/publications/department-for-exiting-the-european-union-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-april-to-june-2017 – 1515 views</p><p>/government/publications/department-for-exiting-the-european-union-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-january-to-march-2017 – 1390 views</p><p>/government/publications/department-for-exiting-the-european-union-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-october-to-december-2016 – 677 views</p><p>/government/publications/department-for-exiting-the-european-union-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings-july-to-september-2016 – 144 views</p><p> </p>","Wycombe","Mr Steve Baker",,"2018-05-03T15:59:04.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891446/answer","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891446/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891446/answer",,,,,,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-04-25","Department for Exiting the European Union: Diaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many page views there were of his Department's Ministerial diaries in each of the last 12 m