"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891447","Treasury","false","2018-05-03","<p>The page<em> ‘HM Treasury: ministerial gifts, hospitality, travel and meetings’, </em>available at https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel’<em>, </em>has received over 1800 views over the past twelve months. These are detailed below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>May-17</p></td><td><p>125</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jun-17</p></td><td><p>88</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jul-17</p></td><td><p>198</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Aug-17</p></td><td><p>92</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sep-17</p></td><td><p>90</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oct-17</p></td><td><p>159</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Nov-17</p></td><td><p>234</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Dec-17</p></td><td><p>280</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Jan-18</p></td><td><p>168</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Feb-18</p></td><td><p>80</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Mar-18</p></td><td><p>197</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Apr-18</p></td><td><p>111</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-05-03T12:51:45.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891447/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891447/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891447/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-25","Treasury: Diaries","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer,  how many page views there were of his Department's Ministerial diaries in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137920"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891448","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-03","<p>Details of Department for Transport ministerial gifts, hospitality, travel and external meetings are published quarterly. This information can be accessed on GOV.UK at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dft-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings#contents" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dft-ministerial-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings</a></p><p> </p><p>To date, the page views for each set of data are:</p><ul><li>January to March 2017 (published 30 June 2017), 57 page views</li><li>April to June 2017 (published 13 October 2017), 61 page views</li><li>July to September 2017 (published 4 December 2017), 165 page views</li><li>October to December 2017 (published 23 March 2018), 152 page views</li></ul><p> </p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-05-03T13:59:52.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891448/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891448/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891448/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-25","Department for Transport: Diaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many page views there were of his Department's Ministerial diaries in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137921"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891449","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-01","<p>Following the Grenfell Tower tragedy we have been working urgently to identify any other buildings over 18 metres with potentially unsafe aluminium composite material (ACM) cladding. With the support of local authorities, fire and rescue services and the expert panel, MHCLG is supporting building owners to take immediate steps to ensure the safety of residents. Homes England is also reviewing the implications where homes may have been purchased with the support of Help to Buy Equity Loan.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab",,"2018-05-01T12:27:45.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891449/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891449/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891449/answer","Esher and Walton","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891449/answer/previousversion/55038","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891449/answer/previousversion/55038","Biography information for Dominic Raab","7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-25","Help to Buy Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what estimate he has made of the loss in value of Help to Buy equity loans owed to the Exchequer as a result of the discovery of unsafe cladding.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","137909"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891450","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-16","<p>Information on Ministry of Justice ministerial gifts, hospitality, travel and meetings is <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/moj-gifts-hospitality-travel-and-meetings" target="_blank">published quarterly</a>, the following data covers quarterly releases for the last 12-months:</p><p> </p><p>To date, the page views for each set of data are as follows:</p><ul><li>The January – March 2017 quarterly release has had <strong>62 unique views* </strong></li><li>The April – June 2017 quarterly release has had <strong>63 unique views* </strong></li><li>The July – September 2017 quarterly release has had <strong>65 unique views*</strong></li><li>The October – December 2017 quarterly release - <strong>Not yet published.</strong></li></ul><p> </p><p><strong>*How many times the data download link has been clicked (unique).</strong></p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-05-16T15:49:31.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891450/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891450/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891450/answer","Penrith and The Border","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891450/answer/previousversion/54715","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891450/answer/previousversion/54715","Biography information for Rory Stewart","54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-25","Ministry of Justice: Diaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many page views there were of his Department's Ministerial diaries in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891451","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Department’s letter of 5 September recommended that local authorities and housing associations check their records for whether strengthening work had been undertaken and/or to undertake surveys of any large panel system buildings which they own.</p><p>The letter referred building owners to a number of reports available to be helpful in understanding how to assess large panel system buildings, including the Handbook for the structural assessment of large panel system dwelling blocks or accidental loading, which was published by the Building Research Establishment in 2012.</p><p>The Department has commissioned the Building Research Establishment to review and update as the Handbook.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","137911","2018-05-03T13:40:41.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891451/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891451/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891451/answer","Esher and Walton","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891451/answer/previousversion/55040","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891451/answer/previousversion/55040","Biography information for Dominic Raab","7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-25","System Building: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department has taken to support local authorities address safety concerns in relation to large panel system buildings since his Department’s letter of 5 September 2017.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","137910"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891452","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-01","<p>Between 30 June 2017 and 29 April 2018, the Department’s data on external Ministerial meetings on Gov.uk was viewed on 802 occasions.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2018-05-01T11:52:22.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891452/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891452/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891452/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-25","Department of Health and Social Care: Diaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many page views there were of his Department's Ministerial diaries in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137923"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891453","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-02","<p><br>The Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government (MHCLG) does not publish ministerial diaries.</p><p>Information on MHCLG ministerial gifts, hospitality, travel and external meetings is published quarterly. To date, the page views for each set of data are as follows:</p><p /> <p>January – March 2017 <strong>370 page views</strong></p><p>April – June 2017 <strong>428 page views</strong></p><p>July – September 2017 <strong>384 page views</strong></p><p>October – December 2017 <strong>165 page views<p><p></strong></p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-05-02T13:35:48.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891453/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891453/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891453/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-25","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Diaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many page views there were of his Department's Ministerial diaries in each of the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137924"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891454","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-04-30","<p>The Department is working with the Care Quality Commission to consider what further action is needed following this report, to ensure we are striking a balance between the provision of safe, effective and high-quality care whilst not stifling innovation.</p><p> </p><p>A cross-regulatory forum has been set up to consider the issues online providers pose for the regulatory model. In addition, NHS England’s clinical safety group will review the recommendations in the report and determine further action for current online services.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-04-30T13:23:42.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891454/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891454/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891454/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-25","Primary Health Care: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps his Department is taking in response to the Care Quality Commission report, The state of care in independent online primary health services.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","137959"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891455","House of Commons Commission","false","2018-04-30","<p>The House Service is currently developing proposals with suppliers for making improvements to the mobile phone signal across the whole estate. This partly relies on the support of the mobile networks, and so far discussions have been held with one of the four mobile networks and Airwave.</p><p>Surveys of the estate have already been completed and a network supplier has started to design a system to improve the cover. Work will start shortly.</p>","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake",,"2018-04-30T12:49:30.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891455/answer","Biography information for Tom Brake","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891455/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891455/answer",,,,,,,,,"18","House of Commons Commission","House of Commons Commission","2018-04-25","Palace of Westminster: Mobile Phones","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Carshalton and Wallington, representing the House of Commons Commission, what steps the Commission is taking to improve cellular phone reception in the Palace of Westminster.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","137960"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891456","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-03","<p>It is the responsibility of each organisation to ensure their compliance with the General Data Protection Regulation which comes into effect on 25 May 2018. For the past year we have been working alongside system partners across health and social care in developing a comprehensive suite of guidance products to help organisations recognise their obligations and help put effective governance and risk management arrangements in place from 25 May. These guidance materials are available to all health and care organisations on the NHS Digital website and will include guidance to general practice, optometry, pharmaceutical and dental organisations. In addition, there is considerable information and guidance available from the Information Commissioner’s Office.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","138069","2018-05-03T13:03:40.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891456/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891456/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891456/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-25","Primary Health Care: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the General Data Protection Regulation on (a) pharmacists, (b) dentists, (c) optometrists, (d) general practitioners and (e) other NHS primary care contractors.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","138068"
