"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890325","Treasury","false","2018-04-27","<p>HMRC does not hold the information requested. HMRC does not hold information that allows them to identify self-invested personal pensions separate from overall personal pensions.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-04-27T10:01:12.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890325/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890325/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890325/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-24","Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the number of firms that operate self-invested personal pension schemes for individuals which have ceased operating within the past two years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","137489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890326","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-02","<p>In delivering the Emergency Services Network (ESN), the mobile network operator EE is delivering around 500 new sites (up to 291 of which will be funded by the Government) and upgrading its entire existing network. Over 300 of these new sites are in Scotland and all new sites are open to incoming site share applications from other Mobile Network Operators. Additionally, in the more remote areas of Great Britain, the Government, as part of its Extended Area Service (EAS) Programme, will deliver approximately 300 further sites for ESN and, potentially, for commercial coverage. 123 of these EAS sites will be in Scotland.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-05-02T13:05:04.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890326/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890326/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-24","Mobile Phones: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of using emergency services masts to improve mobile phone coverage in rural parts of Scotland and the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Alister Jack","Dumfries and Galloway","Mr Alister Jack","137646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890327","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-02","<p>Ministers regularly meet the Mobile Network Operators to discuss a range of issues including improving mobile phone coverage across the whole of the UK, including Scotland.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-05-02T13:06:20.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890327/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890327/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890327/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-24","Mobile Phones: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what recent discussions he has had with mobile phone operators on improving mobile phone coverage in rural parts of Scotland.","false","Biography information for Mr Alister Jack","Dumfries and Galloway","Mr Alister Jack","137647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890328","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-27","<p>Information on Work and Health Programme referrals, attachments and employment outcomes is not currently available.</p><p>We plan to publish statistical information for the Work and Health Programme in Autumn 2018, which will be produced in accordance with the Code of Practice for Official Statistics.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-04-27T14:00:14.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890328/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890328/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890328/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-24","Work and Health Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people have enrolled on the Work and Health Programme; and how many of those people are in employment as a result of enrolling in that programme.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","137468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890329","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-02","<p>The Secretary of State meets regularly with his counterparts in Treasury to discuss a range of matters, including the creative sector tax reliefs, which have successfully encouraged the production of culturally British films and high-end TV programmes worth over £10 billion in expenditure since 2007, making the UK one of the top production destinations in the world.</p><p>We are committed to improving diversity in all DCMS sectors and is supportive of relevant work being undertaken by the British Film Institute (BFI) as the government’s arm’s length body for the moving image.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-05-02T13:09:15.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890329/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890329/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890329/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-24","Film and Television: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what discussions he has had with the Chancellor of the Exchequer on changing (a) film and (b) high-end television tax relief to encourage an increase in the diversity of people working in the film and television industries.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","137503"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890330","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-30","<p>We recognise that there are human rights concerns in India-administered Kashmir. We have recently discussed this situation in India-administered Kashmir with representatives of the Indian Government. We encourage all States to ensure that their domestic laws are in line with international standards. The FCO believes that any allegations of human rights abuses must be investigated thoroughly, promptly and transparently.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-04-30T14:44:28.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890330/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890330/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890330/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-24","Kashmir: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to help tackle alleged human rights abuses in Indian-occupied Kashmir.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","137585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890331","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-04-30","<p>The British Government encourages all states to ensure that their domestic laws meet international human rights standards. We raise the issue of Kashmir, including human rights, with the Governments of India and Pakistan. The British Government also works with the Indian and Pakistani Governments to build capacity and share expertise to tackle challenges, including the promotion and protection of human rights.</p>","Cities of London and Westminster","Mark Field",,"2018-04-30T14:50:53.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890331/answer","Biography information for Mark Field","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890331/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-24","Kashmir: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to help ensure that Commonwealth citizens in disputed Kashmir territories have their human rights upheld.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","137586"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890332","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-17","<p>The Secretary of State for Justice has not had any discussions with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on the implications of the decision of the High Court in <em>Peel Port Shareholder Finance Co v Dornoch Ltd </em>[2017] EWHC 876 (TCC) for the conduct of legal proceedings in relation to which the defendant may have public liability insurance.</p>","South East Cambridgeshire","Lucy Frazer",,"2018-05-17T17:24:07.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890332/answer","Biography information for Lucy Frazer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890332/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890332/answer","Penrith and The Border","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890332/answer/previousversion/54714","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890332/answer/previousversion/54714","Biography information for Rory Stewart","54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-24","Insurance: Liability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on the implications for the public liability claims handling process of the non-disclosure by organisations of their public liability insurer.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","137507"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890333","Attorney General","false","2018-05-21","<p>The Government Legal Department (GLD), Attorney General Office (AGO) and HM Crown Prosecution Service Inspectorate (HM CPSI) engage a centrally managed procurement service in procurements of more than £10,000. For 2016-17 and 2017-18, an examination of records held by the centrally managed procurement service indicated that there were no instances of an invitation to tender where bids were not received.</p><p>Similarly, during the financial years 2016-17 and 2017-18 no invitations to tender by the Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) or the Serious Fraud Office (SFO) exceeding OJEU thresholds received no bidders.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2018-05-21T13:24:55.743Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890333/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890333/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890333/answer","South Swindon","South Swindon","Robert Buckland","Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890333/answer/previousversion/56730","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890333/answer/previousversion/56730","Biography information for Robert Buckland","88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2018-04-24","Attorney General: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890334","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-04-30","<p>We do not hold this information centrally.</p><p> </p><p>To answer this question would incur disproportionate costs.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2018-04-30T16:15:49.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890334/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890334/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890334/answer","Watford","Watford","Richard Harrington","Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890334/answer/previousversion/54703","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890334/answer/previousversion/54703","Biography information for Richard Harrington","201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-24","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890335","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-04-27","<p>At present, prospective claimants may be able to obtain information about insurance cover held by a prospective defendant under the Third Parties (Rights against Insurers) Act 2010 if the defendant is insolvent or in other similar circumstances covered by that Act and under Part 31 of the Civil Procedure Rules, which permits the court to order the pre-action disclosure of documents in appropriate cases.</p><p> </p><p>The Government does not have any plans to change the law in this area.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-04-27T13:51:33.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890335/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890335/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-24","Insurance: Liability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether he has considered the implications for the public liability claims handling process of the non-disclosure by organisations of their public liability insurer.","false","Biography information for Rosie Cooper","West Lancashire","Rosie Cooper","137508"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890336","Cabinet Office","false","2018-05-02","<p>Every tender published in the Official Journal of the EU (OJEU) by the Cabinet Office during the period from April 2016 to March 2018 received bids.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-05-02T15:43:22.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890336/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890336/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890336/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-04-24","Cabinet Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890337","Cabinet Office","false","2018-05-03","<p>Every tender published in the Official Journal of the EU (OJEU) by the Crown Commercial Service during the period from April 2016 to March 2018 received bids.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-05-03T14:10:50.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890337/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890337/answer",,,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-04-24","Crown Commercial Service: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many of the Crown Commercial Service's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137438"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890338","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-02","<p>There has been one such invitation.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2018-05-02T16:34:13.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890338/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890338/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890338/answer",,,,,,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-24","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137439"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890339","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-02","<p>There were no invitations to tender with a value exceeding the Official Journal of the EU (OJEU) thresholds which received no bids during the period from April 2016 to March 2018.</p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry",,"2018-05-02T13:21:50.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890339/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890339/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890339/answer",,,,,,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-24","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890340","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-27","<p>The number of Ministry of Defence invitations to tender that have received no bidders in the last two years is not held centrally and could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-04-27T13:18:26.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890340/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890340/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890340/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-24","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890341","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-02","<p>There were 11 invitations to tender published between 1 April 2016 and 31 March 2018 that received no bidders.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2018-05-02T15:04:52.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890341/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890341/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890341/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-24","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890342","Department for Education","false","2018-05-03","<p>Since April 2016, DfE Commercial have managed in excess of 250 projects. Of these, there have been three projects for which we received no bids and a further two projects, which were split into geographical areas, for which one or more areas received no bids.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton",,"2018-05-03T16:25:58.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890342/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890342/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890342/answer","Guildford","Guildford","Anne Milton","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890342/answer/previousversion/55681","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890342/answer/previousversion/55681","Biography information for Anne Milton","60","Education","Education","2018-04-24","Department for Education: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890343","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-01","<p>During 2016 and 2017, 665 invitations to tender were listed on the Bravo Solution portal with contract values of £25k and over. 48 tenders did not receive bids. <br>​</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-05-01T12:55:21.243Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890343/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890343/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890343/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-24","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890344","Home Office","false","2018-05-02","<p>During Financial Years 16/17 and 17/18, the Home Office issued 2 invitation to tenders, that attracted no bid responses.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-05-02T15:01:34.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890344/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890344/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890344/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-24","Home Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many of her Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890345","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-02","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-05-02T16:13:07.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890345/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890345/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890345/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-24","Ministry of Justice: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890346","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-27","<p>We do not have information on every Universal Credit claimant that has been overpaid or underpaid.</p><p> </p><p>The Department’s latest Fraud and Error estimates can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fraud-and-error-in-the-benefit-system-financial-year-2016-to-2017-estimates" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/fraud-and-error-in-the-benefit-system-financial-year-2016-to-2017-estimates</a>. The statistics are based on a sample of around 1,100 cases selected randomly from the UC caseload during 2016-17.</p><p> </p><p>Of the overpayments identified within this sample, the median overpayment was £110 per month, with the smallest being £0.01 and the largest being £820. Of the underpayments identified in the sample, the median underpayment was £30 per month, with the smallest being £0.01 and the largest £600.</p><p> </p><p>These statistics also show that £90m of Universal Credit expenditure was overpaid in 2016-17. The rate of overpayments due to fraud on Universal Credit is 3.2%, which accounted for approximately £50m of this total.</p><p> </p><p>Total underpayments for Universal Credit in 2016-17 amounted to £20m. The rate of underpayments due to official error in Universal Credit is 0.9%, a decrease from 1.2% in 2015/16. The rate of underpayments on Universal Credit due to claimant error is 0.4%, an increase of 0.2% from 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p>The Department’s preliminary Fraud and Error National Statistics for 2017-18 will be published on 17 May 2018.</p><p> </p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-04-27T13:13:44.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890346/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890346/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890346/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-24","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number of universal credit claimants that have been (a) overpaid and (b) underpaid; what the value of the largest of each such payments was; and and what the total amount (i) overpaid and (ii) underpaid was in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","137469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890347","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-04-30","<p>My Department uses two centres of procurement excellence for all procurement action who manage the tender process on behalf of the client. Details on returning tenders are not held by the department.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-04-30T14:42:15.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890347/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890347/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890347/answer",,,,,,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-04-24","Northern Ireland Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many of her Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890348","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-27","<p>The information requested is not readily available and to provide it would incur disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>However, we know that the Real Time Information (RTI) system is working well with over 99% of individual employment records now being reported in real time. This method of sharing information is allowing us to run a welfare system that is responsive to changes in earnings and helps us identify cases of fraud. Only a small proportion of the 1% of remaining cases are referred to HMRC to clarify those earnings with the employer.</p><p> </p><p>DWP work closely with HMRC to investigate any risks associated with RTI data, and jointly deal with disputes arising when claimants query their reported earnings. As DWP receives copies of the data submitted by employers, the risk of data corruption within HMRC is regarded as minimal. However, DWP and HMRC continually monitor the data and no significant problems have been identified.</p><p> </p><p>A number of processes are in place to deal with inaccurate data from employers. DWP and HMRC analysts monitor the RTI data received, looking for trends, patterns and causes. Both Departments then work together with employers and partners, such as software developers and payroll bureaux, to improve the quality of the data.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-04-27T10:31:10.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890348/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890348/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890348/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-24","Universal Credit: ICT","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many in-work universal credit claimants have received an incorrect award for reasons involving the real time information system.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","137470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890349","Scotland Office","false","2018-05-01","<p>Other than for minor or bespoke purchases, the Scotland Office does not normally undertake direct procurement or tendering of external agencies or consultant contracts. It utilises existing service contracts between suppliers and the Scottish Government, Cabinet Office or the Ministry of Justice.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-05-01T11:53:27.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890349/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890349/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890349/answer",,,,,,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-04-24","Scotland Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890350","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-27","<p>The number of invitations to tender that have received no bidders in the last two years are as follows:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>DfTc</strong></p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>DVLA</strong></p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>DVSA</strong></p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>VCA</strong></p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>MCA</strong></p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani",,"2018-04-27T11:06:25.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890350/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890350/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890350/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-24","Department for Transport: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890351","Treasury","false","2018-05-01","<p>The information requested could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>To provide the requested information HM Treasury would need to manually review all of the documentation relating to procurements undertaken in the last 2 years, checking individual tender responses.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-05-01T14:36:05.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890351/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890351/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890351/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-04-24","Treasury: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many of his Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137450"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890352","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-27","<p>The information requested is not available as no data is held on the number using the signposting to food bank service at Jobcentres. Jobcentre Plus does not make direct referrals to food banks but has offered a signposting service since 2011 to those who have expressed an interest in using a food bank.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-27T09:03:46.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890352/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890352/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890352/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-24","Jobcentres: Food Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of claimants signposted by Jobcentre Plus to food banks were previously (a) offered and (b) awarded an advance payment or short term benefit advance.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","137471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890353","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-27","<p>In the two year period to 25<sup>th</sup> of April 2018, one Invitation to Tender issued by the Department for Work and Pensions received no bidders.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2018-04-27T09:00:47.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890353/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890353/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890353/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-24","Department for Work and Pensions: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many of her Department's invitations to tender have received no bidders in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","137451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890354","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-27","<p>Universal Credit provides an unprecedented level of personalised support. People receive tailored support, based on their individual requirements, including financial support.</p><p> </p><p>Repayment of Universal Credit advances are included in the 40% cap on deductions that can be made from a claimant’s award. The maximum rate of deduction for an advance cannot exceed 40% of the claimant’s standard allowance.</p><p> </p><p>These deductions are taken when it is in the best interest of the claimant. In determining this, the Decision Maker will take into account the claimant’s circumstances.</p><p> </p><p>To protect vulnerable claimants from being made homeless or having their fuel disconnected, deductions in excess of the 40% of the claimant’s standard allowance can be taken in some circumstances. This is only for ‘last resort’ deductions , such as for arrears of service charges, rent, gas and electricity and on-going monthly costs of gas and electricity.</p><p> </p><p>If a claimant is in financial difficulty as a result of the level of deductions, where it relates to benefit debt, a social fund loan or rent arrears, they can request that a reduction be considered.</p><p> </p><p>If a claimant is having difficulty repaying a benefit overpayment they can request a reconsideration of the amount that is being taken. Any reduction will be based on the individual circumstances of the claimant rather than the amount of the overpayment, which helps to ensure that a sustainable repayment plan based on affordability is put in place.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2018-04-27T13:10:05.573Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890354/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890354/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890354/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-24","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the maximum amount deducted was, as a proportion of each award from universal credit claimants to repay advance payments and historic debt from sources including the Social Fund.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","137472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890355","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-02","<p>The Government already advises motorcyclists to wear high visibility clothing - Rules 86 and 87 of the Highway Code includes the advice to “wear a light or brightly coloured helmet and fluorescent clothing or strips, in daylight” and “wear reflective clothing or strips to improve your visibility in the dark”.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has no plans to bring forward proposals to make compulsory the use of reflective or fluorescent clothing for motorcyclists.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-05-02T15:23:14.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890355/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890355/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890355/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-24","Motorcycles: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has plans to (a) bring forward legislative proposals to make compulsory and (b) promote the use of reflective or fluorescent clothing for motorbike riders.","false","Biography information for Vicky Ford","Chelmsford","Vicky Ford","137678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890356","Women and Equalities","false","2018-05-14","<p>The Equality Act 2010 requires service providers and employers, including public authorities, to make reasonable adjustments to ensure that disabled people are not put at a substantial disadvantage, including in questions of access. For service providers this is an anticipatory duty, which means that they should not wait until they are asked to make an adjustment. However, the duty does not require publication of information about any adjustments made or the general accessibility features of a building, such as those required by building regulations.</p><p> </p><p>The Government agrees that the public sector can play an important leadership role in providing accessibility information for building users, whether they are visitors or employees. However, the Government believes that such decisions are best made at a local level and has no plans to introduce a requirement for such information to be published.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-05-14T16:02:48.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890356/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890356/answer",,,,,,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-04-24","Public Buildings: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities whether she plans to require Departments and local councils to publish the provisions that they have in place for disabled access to their buildings; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Sir Mark Hendrick","137466"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890357","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-04","<p>In line with international reporting guidelines a number of different data sources are combined to calculate the emissions from waste incineration sites for the National Atmospheric Emissions Inventory.</p><p> </p><p>These include emissions data from large waste installations reported under the Industrial Emissions Directive and European Pollution Release and Transfer Register and emissions calculated from peer reviewed literature emission factors and activity data.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2018-05-04T13:16:41.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890357/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890357/answer",,,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-24","Incinerators","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what methodology was used in the National Atmospheric Emissions Inventory to calculate the emissions of (a) PM 0.1, (b) PM 1, (c) PM 2.5 and (d) PM 10 from waste incineration sites.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","137400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890358","Department for Transport","false","2018-04-27","<p>Network Rail are embedded in the rail franchising process throughout, including through the secondment of Network Rail staff to franchise project teams to provide a clear conduit for Network Rail advice and expertise.</p><p> </p><p>With the publication of the Strategic Vision for Rail in November 2017, the Secretary of State set out plans to ‘end the operational divide between track and train and to establish a new generation of integrated regional rail operations’.</p><p>a) Joining up operational and communication teams between Network Rail and Train Operating Companies will improve performance, communication with passengers and restoration of services after disruption. Bringing Network Rail and the TOC closer together would mean they run better on a day-to-day basis, and would make it easier to meet the challenges today’s network faces.</p><p> </p><p>b) TOCs are best placed to understand the needs of passengers and therefore to develop plans for improving rail infrastructure that will secure the greatest benefits for passengers. Both the infrastructure manager and train operator would work together with a shared vision. Giving TOCs a role in infrastructure (working closely with Network Rail) will prompt them to act as stewards for the rail network and win greatest possible benefits for passengers.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson","137572","2018-04-27T10:58:09.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890358/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890358/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890358/answer",,,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-24","Railways: Franchises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what role Network Rail has in the rail franchising process; and what recent assessment he has made of the effectiveness of Network Rail in carrying out that role.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","137571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890359","Home Office","false","2018-06-26","<p>UIN 136120 was answered on 10th May 2018 and UIN 136440 was answered on 26th June 2018.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-06-26T15:32:10Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890359/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890359/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890359/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-24","Home Office: Written Questions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans to respond to Questions 136120 and 136440 tabled for a named day on 17 and 18 April 2018 respectively.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","137425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890360","Home Office","false","2018-04-30","<p>A comprehensive assessment was carried out to inform the decision to award the contract to produce UK passports, as part of the procurement process, and this included analysis within a number of areas. The information captured within these assessments is commercially sensitive and the Home Office has no plans to publish this information on that basis.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-04-30T15:11:31.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890360/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890360/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890360/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-24","Passports: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether her Department has produced an impact assessment of the decision on the new contract to produce UK passports.","false","Biography information for John Spellar","Warley","John Spellar","137426"
