"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890544","Department for International Development","false","2018-05-01","<p>The UK is committed to ensuring that any refugee returns to Syria are voluntary, safe, with dignity, and in line with international law. We do not support any forced returns before Syria or parts of Syria are assessed as safe by the UN, which it is yet to do so.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-05-01T16:33:19.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890544/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890544/answer",,,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-04-24","Syria: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether the Government supports the right of Syrian refugees voluntarily to return to Syria.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","137407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890545","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-04-27","<p>The Department plans to publish the update to the &quot;Equality analysis for the Future of Access to Work&quot; which considers the impact of raising the annual limit on Access to work Awards to £57,200 per annum from April 2018 shortly after the end of the pre-election period for the forthcoming local Government elections being held on 3rd May 2018.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton",,"2018-04-27T14:01:43.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890545/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890545/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890545/answer",,,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-24","Access to Work Programme: Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 3 April 2018 to Question 133974, on Access to Work Programme, when her Department plans to publish its update to the Equality Analysis.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","137415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890546","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-04-27","<p>The Submarine Delivery Agency (SDA) Framework Document sets out the composition of the SDA Board, which is to include a maximum of three Government non-Executive Directors (NEDs) and at least three independent NEDs. Currently, two Government NEDs are members of the Board. Following an extensive external recruitment process, we have identified four suitable candidates with the right skills and experience to fulfil the independent NED roles. Announcements will be made when all appointment formalities have been completed.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb",,"2018-04-27T13:17:07.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890546/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890546/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/890546/answer",,,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-04-24","Submarine Delivery Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to page 9 of the Submarine Delivery Agency Corporate Plan 2018-2019, whether three Government non-executive directors and three independent non-executive directors have been appointed to the Submarine Delivery Agency Board.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","137501"
